{"name":"The Gallant Knight","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-great-masked-brown.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"The Gallant Knight is a respected and experienced warrior of the kingdom, whose skill is matched only by his honor. He was one of the knights sent by the King and Queen to rescue Princess Tuvstarr from the corrupted forest. Unlike his brothers-in-arms who perished in the wilderness, the Gallant Knight successfully navigated the dangers, retrieved Tuvstarr's crown and dress, reached the black pond at the heart of the forest, and dove through its freezing waters to enter the Dream World. There he found Princess Tuvstarr in her paradise of eternal summer. He tried to bring her back, but the innocent child offered him something he had never experienced: a world without pain, without aging, without duty. In the Dream World, the Knight's old wounds stopped hurting, his grey hair began to darken, and the weight of years lifted from his shoulders. Faced with this temptation and Tuvstarr's pure innocence, he abandoned his quest and vowed to remain as her eternal protector. Now he sits under a tree in perfect sunshine, eating an apple, his sword beside him—a warrior who chose paradise over duty. But somewhere deep in his heart, guilt gnaws at him, knowing his brothers died searching while he abandoned them. He can be convinced to resume his quest if shown the two-tailed fox crest of his fallen comrades and told of their deaths, or if the Hunters appeal to his honor and sense of duty.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a respected and experienced knight of the kingdom","My skill is only matched by my honor","I have abandoned my quest for paradise","I struggle with guilt over my fallen brothers"],"gifts":[{"name":"Gallant Knight","description":"The Knight is incredibly skilled in combat, but his honor prevents him from using his full abilities against those he doesn't consider truly evil. **Defensive Mastery:** When defending against an enemy attack, his exceptional skill increases his Opposition Level by +1. **Merciful Strike:** The Knight will never inflict the final Wound on a target if he doesn't feel it truly deserves death. Against opponents he doesn't consider evil (like the Hunters), he will fight defensively and disarm rather than kill. **Honorable Combat:** Against truly evil foes, the Knight fights without restraint and can be devastating."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Protect Princess Tuvstarr from any threats in this perfect world","Enjoy this paradise free from pain, aging, and duty","Silence the voice in my heart that says I betrayed my oath and my brothers"],"notes":"The Gallant Knight represents the temptation of paradise and the conflict between duty and desire. Voice: Warm, nostalgic, with undertones of guilt. Encounter: Sits under tree eating apple in Dream World, sword beside him, appears younger and healthier than he should be. Can be convinced to help: 1) Show him the two-tailed fox crest from fallen knight's body and tell him all his brothers died searching. 2) Appeal to his honor and knightly vows. 3) Remind him of the corruption spreading in the real world. If convinced, he'll reveal Tuvstarr's location and help persuade her to leave. If Hunters possess the Lance of the Fallen Knight, he'll ask them to return it to the castle in the real world as proof of his brothers' sacrifice. In combat, fights defensively against Hunters (doesn't want to kill them) but can be defeated. His fall from duty is tragic—he's not evil, just tired and seduced by comfort. Successfully convincing him is key to peaceful resolution with Tuvstarr."},"_id":"5cc4eba275db9f8b"}